                    	<note xml:id="n_transcrSource" type="transcrSource">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Original manuscript</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Date of postmark: Tuesday, 30 May 1882. Jo van Gogh-Bonger dated it 31 May in <hi rend="italics">Brieven </hi>1914 – she probably based this on the Paris postmark, which is also on the postcard (the other occasion when she adopted the date of the received stamp was with <ref target="let872.xml">letter 872</ref>).</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Postcard (5 cents). Postmarks: ‘’SGRAVENHAGE 9-10 V / 30 MEI 82’ and ‘PARIS 3 (60) 3 / 1E.31 MAI 82’. It is addressed to ‘Monsieur Th. van Gogh/ 5 Rue de Laval/ <hi rend="italics">Paris.</hi>’ Van Gogh probably wrote in English because the card could be read by anyone; cf. in this connection <ref target="let223.xml">letter 223</ref>.</p>
                                    
                                
                    	</note>
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="ogtnotes">
                    
